Package: SampleMultiCat
Title: Sample Size Calculation for Ordinal and Multinomial Outcomes
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: 
    person('Victor J.', 'Vera-Ponce', email = 'victor_jvp@hotmail.com', role = c('aut', 'cre'))
Description: Bilingual (English/Spanish) calculator for sample size in regression
    models with polytomous outcomes. Supports proportional odds ordinal logistic
    regression (using worst cumulative cut EPP approach) and multinomial logistic
    regression (using EPPm criterion from de Jong et al. 2019). The parameter k
    refers to total regression parameters (degrees of freedom), not the number
    of variables. Includes optional power-based calculations via Hmisc::posamsize
    and post-hoc validation of effective EPP/EPPm for published studies.
